## UI components\
\
### Layout width\
The widget container is 680px wide. Use `repeat(auto-fit\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  minmax(160px\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  1fr))` for responsive columns \'97 auto-fit lets the grid pick column count by available width.\
\
### Aesthetic\
Flat\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  clean\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  white surfaces. Minimal \cf7 \strokec7 0\cf4 \strokec4 .5px borders. Generous whitespace. No gradients\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  no shadows (except functional focus rings). Everything should feel native to claude.ai \'97 like it belongs on the page\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  not embedded from somewhere else.\
\
### Tokens\
- Borders: always `\cf7 \strokec7 0\cf4 \strokec4 .5px solid var(--color-border-tertiary)` (or `-secondary` for emphasis)\
- Corner radius: `var(--border-radius-md)` for most elements\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  `var(--border-radius-lg)` for cards\
- Cards: white bg (`var(--color-background-primary)`)\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  \cf7 \strokec7 0\cf4 \strokec4 .5px border\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  radius-lg\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  padding 1rem \cf7 \strokec7 1\cf4 \strokec4 .25rem\
- Form elements (input\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  select\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  textarea\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  button\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  range slider) are pre-styled \'97 write bare tags. Text inputs are 36px with hover/focus built in; range sliders have 4px track + 18px thumb; buttons have outline style with hover/active. Only add inline styles to override (e.g.\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  different width).\
- Buttons: pre-styled with transparent bg\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  \cf7 \strokec7 0\cf4 \strokec4 .5px border-secondary\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  hover bg-secondary\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  active scale(\cf7 \strokec7 0.98\cf4 \strokec4 ). If it triggers sendPrompt\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  append a \uc0\u8599  arrow.\
- **Round every displayed number.** JS float math leaks artifacts \'97 `\cf7 \strokec7 0.1\cf4 \strokec4  + \cf7 \strokec7 0.2\cf4 \strokec4 ` gives `\cf7 \strokec7 0.30000000000000004\cf4 \strokec4 `\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  `\cf7 \strokec7 7\cf4 \strokec4  * \cf7 \strokec7 1.1\cf4 \strokec4 ` gives `\cf7 \strokec7 7.700000000000001\cf4 \strokec4 `. Any number that reaches the screen (slider readouts\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  stat card values\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  axis labels\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  data-point labels\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  tooltips\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  computed totals) must go through `Math.round()`\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  `.toFixed(n)`\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  or `Intl.NumberFormat`. Pick the precision that makes sense for the context \'97 integers for counts\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  \cf7 \strokec7 1\cf4 \strokec4 \'96\cf7 \strokec7 2\cf4 \strokec4  decimals for percentages\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  `toLocaleString()` for currency. For range sliders\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  also set `step=\cf5 \strokec5 "1"\cf4 \strokec4 ` (or step=\cf5 \strokec5 "0.1"\cf4 \strokec4  etc.) so the input itself emits round values.\
- Spacing: use rem for vertical rhythm (1rem\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  \cf7 \strokec7 1\cf4 \strokec4 .5rem\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  2rem)\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  px for component-internal gaps (8px\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  12px\cf2 \strokec2 ,\cf4 \strokec4  16px)\
